\
16. President Donald Trump fired Coast Guard Commandant Admiral Linda Fagan over DEI policies (2025-01-21): Removing the Coast Guard\'92s first woman commandant for an alleged focus on diversity sent a message that senior military careers depend on ideological alignment with the president\'92s stance on inclusion.\
\
17. President Donald Trump fired the TSA head and aviation security advisory members (2025-01-23): The abrupt dismissal of TSA leadership and its advisory committee weakened institutional continuity in aviation security and suggested a willingness to upend expert bodies for political reasons.\
\
18. President Donald Trump ordered a review of FEMA for alleged political bias (2025-01-20): Trump\'92s directive to scrutinize FEMA for partisan bias, followed by talk of dismantling the agency, positioned disaster management structures as potential political adversaries rather than neutral service providers.\
\
19. President Donald Trump fired or sidelined multiple inspectors general and civil watchdogs (2025-01-24): A reported purge of inspectors general across agencies weakened independent oversight mechanisms that normally check executive misconduct and protect whistleblowers.\
\
20. National Treasury Employees Union sued to block Trump\'92s Schedule F reclassification order (2025-01-21): The NTEU lawsuit argued that reclassifying thousands of civil servants as at\uc0\u8209 will political appointees violated due process, using the courts to defend a merit\u8209 based federal workforce against politicization.\
